# Reference for the Release workflow's configuration.
#
# The release builds are intentionally UNSIGNED — this project does not use paid
# code-signing certificates (see docs/RELEASE.md), so the pipeline needs no Apple
# or Windows signing/notarization secrets. The only credential it uses is
# GITHUB_TOKEN, which GitHub Actions provides automatically. There is nothing to
# set here today.
#
# If code signing is ever adopted, the Apple/Windows certificate secret names
# (set under repo Settings → Secrets and variables → Actions) would be documented
# here — and wired into the tauri-action step in .github/workflows/release.yml.
